Six people including a police officer died along the Naivasha-Mai Mahiu Road this morning in two separate accidents.  In the first accident, a security van transporting cash to a local bank collided head-on with a trailer near Jikake IDP camp, killing a police officer and two security guards.  In the second incident near Mai Mahiu town, three youths died on the spot after a motorcycle they were riding on was hit by a car.  Naivasha OCPD Samuel Waweru said the bodies have been taken to Naivasha Sub-County Hospital mortuary. By Titus Too | 2 days ago By Edward Kosut | 2 days ago By Edward Kosut | 3 days ago By Lynn Kolongei | 3 days ago